  "prompt": "Why should you not flush a tampon down the toilet?",
  "response": "Flushing tampons down the toilet is not recommended for several important reasons:\n\n1. **Plumbing Issues**: Tampons can cause clogs in plumbing systems. Unlike human waste, tampons do not break down easily in water and can create blockages in pipes or drainage systems, leading to costly repairs.\n\n2. **Environmental Impact**: Flushing tampons contributes to pollution in wastewater systems. Even if they make it through your plumbing, tampons can end up in oceans and waterways, harming marine life and ecosystems.\n\n3. **Wastewater Treatment Problems**: Many wastewater treatment facilities are not equipped to handle non-biodegradable products like tampons. This can increase the burden on treatment systems and affect the quality of treated water.\n\n4. **Health Hazards**: Tampons can also pose health risks if they cause sewage backups, leading to exposure to potentially harmful bacteria and other pathogens.\n\nInstead of flushing, it\u2019s best to dispose of tampons in a trash bin, using a wrapper or a disposal bag if needed to contain odors.",
